        <cdata>
          <text>&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;One Vote One Choice Act&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;This bill prohibits states from using ranked-choice voting in federal elections. Ranked-choice voting is a system that allows voters to rank multiple candidates on a ballot in order of preference.&lt;/p&gt;</text>
        </cdata>
      </summary>
